libwaitzar - A library for the WaitZar language model (for the Burmese/Myanmar language)

This is the encapsulation API for the WaitZar Burmese language model.
It was programmed in C++, and tested on Windows and Linux.
The package was developed on Debian Linux, and is used heavily 
in the scim-waitzar IMEngine. 

The WaitZar project's home page is:
  http://code.google.com/p/scim-waitzar/

A simple example file is included with the source, or can be downloaded from:
  http://waitzar.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/cross_platform_library/ExternalModelTester.cpp
More information can be found in the API documentation:
  http://waitzar.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/cross_platform_library/Wait_Zar_Model_API.html

Automake & Autoconf files are based on the examples given online at:
http://www.openismus.com/documents/linux/building_libraries/building_libraries.shtml
